  <prompt>Existing schedule data lives in sprk_analysisplaybook.sprk_configjson. Decide: (a) leave there + PlaybookSchedulerJob reads both sources, OR (b) one-time migrate to sprk_backgroundjob.sprk_configjson. Per spec.md FR-2.8, treat scheduler as a thin adapter — leave configjson in playbook entity, scheduler job reads it.</prompt>
  <goal>PlaybookSchedulerJob reads schedule cadence from sprk_analysisplaybook.sprk_configjson (existing source of truth). sprk_backgroundjob row for the scheduler has its own cron (e.g. */15 * * * *) for the parent fire interval.</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">PlaybookSchedulerService becomes a thin adapter; preserves existing config layout</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <topic>playbook-config-schedule-migration</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/dataverse/entity-operations.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-platform-foundations-r3/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check</step>
    <step order="1">Verify PlaybookSchedulerJob reads sprk_analysisplaybook.sprk_configjson correctly</step>
    <step order="2">Seed sprk_backgroundjob row for scheduler with parent cron</step>
    <step order="3">Smoke test: all 7 playbooks discovered on dev tenant; cadence preserved</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">7 active playbooks discovered + scheduled correctly</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Existing sprk_configjson layout preserved (no data migration needed)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
